 LedFly Canopies presents this year’s annual fundraising. All vehicles with a good ground clearance and Diff Lock are welcome to enter. Registration time for vehicles is at 06:00 and the starting time of the race is 08:00.
Entries are R300 per vehicle. There will be a social function with live entertainment, as well as the prize giving at 17:30, at the Conference Centre. Braai packs and side dishes are available at R95 per person (order at registration). For more information call Priscilla on 082 894 3134, or send an email to priscilla@barthea.co.za, or call Jenene on 061 466 4772 or email jenene@offtrax.co.za. • Xeroderma Pigmentosum, or XP, is an autosomal recessive genetic disorder of DNA repair, in which the ability to repair damage caused by ultraviolet (UV) light is deficient. In extreme cases, all exposure to sunlight is forbidden, no matter how small, and as such, individuals with the disease are often colloquially referred to as ‘Children of the Night’.